data.description: Check out this charming 1.5-story home in the Oak Park neighborhood of the Kansas City School District. This property has two bedrooms and one bathroom, making it ideal for those looking for a cozy place to call home, or it could be an excellent investment opportunity! As you step inside, you'll be greeted by the main floor, which has two living areas. Except for the kitchen, the entire main-level floor is covered in wood flooring, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. A lovely fireplace complements the living room. Second living/family room has plenty of space for entertaining guests, so you'll never be short on space for social gatherings. There are two comfortable bedrooms on the main level, one of which is the primary bedroom. This floor also has a full bathroom, which ensures everyone's comfort and functionality. Upstairs, you'll find two more rooms that, depending on your preferences and needs, can be converted into bedrooms or office spaces. This home has over 1800 square feet of living space and plenty of room for customization. The basement also provides an opportunity to increase the property's value by finishing it to your liking. The sewer pipes have been redone, and the furniture on the property remains. The backyard has a gazebo that will stay as well with the property, providing a nice outdoor space for relaxation! This home shows timeless charm and character, making it an excellent choice for a first-time buyer or a savvy investor looking for their next profitable venture!
